'''Double-T armature''' - Shape of [[Armature (electrical engineering)|armature]] used in some motors and generators.<ref name=IOEM>[http://www.eti.kit.edu/english/1390.php The invention of the electric motor 1856-1893]</ref> Two 'T' shapes extending from axis.

Its use in early Siemens dynamos caused a pulsing variable DC output which was improved upon by the [[Gramme dynamo]].<ref name=IOEM/>

Another improvement is the three-pole armature ('triple-T' armature) as in this image :
