'''HeiQ Materials AG''' (German pronunciation:  [ˈhaɪkju]) is a Swiss specialty chemistry company, headquartered in Zurich, Switzerland. It was founded in 2005 as a [[University spin-off|spin-off]] of [[Swiss Federal Institute of Technology Zurich|Swiss Federal Institute of Technology Zurich (ETH)]].

HeiQ produces and sells textile finishing and other [[Speciality chemicals|auxiliaries]]. But its core business activity is to conduct co-joint research and development projects with consumer textile products brands or textile producers for [[textile finishing]] to achieve effects that are currently not in market or not optimized to certain products.

For the [[Deepwater Horizon oil spill]] that began in April 2010 in the [[Gulf of Mexico]], HeiQ, TWE Group and Beyond Surface Technologies jointly developed an oil-absorbing, water-repelling, nonwoven fabric, in the name Oilguard <ref>{{cite web|url=http://oilguard.org/|title=Oilguard|website=oilguard.org}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.handelszeitung.ch/unternehmen-1473|title=Handelszeitung.ch {{!}} Aktuelle Nachrichten und Hintergründe zu Wirtschaft, Politik und Börsen|access-date=2016-08-26}}</ref> for oil relief efforts.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://af.reuters.com/article/idAFLDE65S0UX20100629|title=Swiss firm has plan to save coastlines from oil|first=Reuters|last=Editorial|publisher=}}</ref> The product was intended for beach protection against oil spills and was applied to the shoreline. This allows for the fabric to absorb crude oil while repelling the seawater. This innovation was rewarded the Swiss Technology Award (2010)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.land-der-erfinder.ch/?p=7815|title=Die Erfindung Oilguard von HeiQ {{!}} Land der Erfinder – Das Schweizer Magazin für Innovationen|website=www.land-der-erfinder.ch|access-date=2016-08-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nzz.ch/oilguard-vliesstoff-erhaelt-auszeichnung-1.8276869|title=Swiss Technology Award für HeiQ: Oilguard-Vliesstoff erhält Auszeichnung|date=2010-11-04|newspaper=Neue Zürcher Zeitung|language=de-CH|issn=0376-6829|access-date=2016-08-26}}</ref> and the Swiss Award (2013).<ref>{{Citation|title=Friedenskämpferin Bineta Diop gewinnt "SwissAward"|date=2013-01-11|url=http://www.srf.ch/sendungen/unterhaltungssendungen/events-shows/swissaward/friedenskaempferin-bineta-diop-gewinnt-swissaward-2|publisher=Schweizer Radio und Fernsehen SRF|language=de-CH|accessdate=2016-08-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.venturelab.ch/index.cfm?page=133022&article_id=1040|title=HeiQ-Gründer für den Swiss Award nominiert|website=www.venturelab.ch|access-date=2016-08-26}}</ref> The water-repelling property of Oilguard is achieved with a textile finishing that creates the [[Lotus effect|Lotus Effect]] on the surface of the [[non-woven]] fabric. The [[Fluorine|non-fluorinated]] finishing makes the fabric only water repellent but not oil repellent, therefore the fabric absorbs oil crudes but not the seawater.

The company also has three subsidiaries in the United States, Hong Kong and Australia, known as HeiQ ChemTex, HeiQ Ltd. and HeiQ Australia Pty. Ltd. respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.heiq.com|title=HeiQ Materials AG – SWISS TECH INSIDE|website=www.heiq.com}}</ref>

